Package com.atakmap.map.layer.raster.tilereader

Class TileReader

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.atakmap.map.layer.raster.tilereader.TileReader
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Controls
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractTilePyramidTileReader, AndroidTileReader, DRGTileReader, GdalTileReader, SQLiteSingleTileReader
    public abstract class TileReader
extends java.lang.Object
implements Controls
    Provides tile-based access to raster data. Synchronous and asynchronous data access methods are provided.

    Data returned is intended for visualization purposes and the allowed pixel formats represent this.

      • read

        public TileReader.ReadResult read​(int level,
                                  long tileColumn,
                                  long tileRow,
                                  byte[] data)
        Reads the specified tile at the specified level and stores the data in the specified array. The returned data will have dimensions consistent with getTileWidth(int, long) and getTileHeight(int, long) for the specified level, tile column and tile row.
        Parameters:
        level - The resolution level
        tileColumn - The tile column
        tileRow - The tile row
        data - Output buffer for the data of the specified tile
        Returns:
        true if the read completed successfuly, false if the operation was canceled asynchronously

      • read

                                           long srcY,
                                           long srcW,
                                           long srcH,
                                           int dstW,
                                           int dstH,
                                           byte[] buf)
        Reads an arbitrary region of the image at an arbitrary scale. The source data will be scaled to meet dstW and dstH.
        Parameters:
        srcX - The source (unscaled) x-coordinate of the region
        srcY - The source (unscaled) y-coordinate of the region
        srcW - The source (unscaled) width of the region
        srcH - The source (unscaled) height of the region
        dstW - The output width
        dstH - The output size
        buf - Output buffer for the data of the specified tile
        Returns:
        true if the read completed successfuly, false if the operation was canceled asynchronously

        protected void cancel()
        Implements asynchronous cancel. This method is invoked by the actively servicing TileReader.ReadRequest and should never be invoked externally.

        The default implementation returns immediately.

      • dispose

        public final void dispose()
        Disposes the TileReader and releases any allocated resources. Any pending asynchronous read requests will be aborted. The user should always cancel any in-progress asynchronous read request before invoking this method to avoid having to wait for the request to complete before this method can return.

      • dispose

        @Deprecated
@DeprecatedApi(since="4.9",
               forRemoval=true,
               removeAt="4.12")
public final void dispose​(java.lang.Runnable releaseHook)
        Deprecated.
        use dispose()
        Disposes the TileReader and releases any allocated resources. Any pending asynchronous read requests will be aborted. The user should always cancel any in-progress asynchronous read request before invoking this method to avoid having to wait for the request to complete before this method can return.
        Parameters:
        releaseHook - If non-null, a hook that will be executed on the TileReader.AsynchronousIO thread after all pending read requests have been aborted.

      • disposeImpl

        protected void disposeImpl()
        Implementation specific disposal. Implementations should always invoke super.disposeImpl().

        The default implementation marks valid as false.

        This method will always be externally synchronized on this.readLock.

      • isMultiResolution

        public boolean isMultiResolution()
        Returns a flag indicating whether or not the source is multi-resolution. If true the source can decode the image at resolutions other than the native resolution without subsampling. If false all tiles at a resolution other than the native resolution must be subsampled.

        Use of a TileCache does not make a TileReader multi-resolution.

        Returns:
        true if the source contains tiles at multiple resolutions, false otherwise.

      • getMinCacheLevel

        public final int getMinCacheLevel()
        Returns the minimum RSET level where the tile cache will be employed. Any requested level less than the returned value will be read and subsampled directly from the dataset every time.
        Returns:

      • asReadCallback

        protected TileCache.ReadCallback asReadCallback​(TileReader.ReadRequest request)

      • start

        public void start()
        Instructs the TileReader that more than one tile may be consecutively requested.

        This merely serves as a hint to the reader; tiles may be requested regardless of whether start() had previously been invoked.

      • stop

        public void stop()
        Instructs the TileReader that the bulk requests indicated by start() will cease.

        This merely serves as a hint to the reader; tiles may continue to be requested even after stop() has been invoked.

      • getTileVersion

        public long getTileVersion​(int level,
                           long tileColumn,
                           long tileRow)
        Returns the version for the specified tile. This value may change over the duration of the runtime, indicating that tiles previously read with a different version are not the most up-to-date and should be reloaded. Version numbers should be monotonically increasing.
        Parameters:
        level - The level
        tileColumn - The tile column
        tileRow - The tile row
        Returns:
        The current tiles version. The default implementation always returns 0
